  "title": "Optometrist (Retail) - Islandwide - 5 days/ week [GC]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Refraction Testing &amp; Dispensing</strong>: Perform accurate eye examinations and refraction tests; dispense appropriate optical products based on prescriptions.</li>\n  <li><strong>Contact Lens Expertise</strong>: Proficient in contact lens fitting, dispensing, aftercare, and identifying contact lens-related complications.</li>\n  <li><strong>Customer Advisory</strong>: Provide professional advice to customers on spectacle lenses, frames, coatings, and other optical products to suit their needs and preferences.</li>\n  <li><strong>Customer Service Excellence</strong>: Deliver exceptional service to ensure a positive and personalized shopping experience.</li>\n  <li><strong>Store Operations &amp; Inventory Management</strong>: Assist in daily store operations, maintain cleanliness and visual merchandising, and ensure accurate inventory control.</li>\n  <li><strong>Brand Representation</strong>: Act as a Brand Ambassador, upholding the company’s image, values, and service standards.</li>\n  <li><strong>Sales Performance</strong>: Meet individual KPIs and actively contribute to achieving overall store sales targets.</li>\n  <li><strong>Cashiering &amp; Transactions</strong>: Handle various in-store payment methods accurately and efficiently.</li>\n  <li><strong>Product Knowledge &amp; SOP Compliance</strong>: Stay updated on the latest products and promotions while adhering strictly to company SOPs and retail standards.<br>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Registered (Fully/ Pre-) with the Singapore Optometrists and Opticians Board (OOB).</li>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Optometry.</li>\n  <li>Fresh graduates are welcome, training is provided.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
